    <abstract>p. 28-29: The material of base and the head of the sutra stone in Fukuoka, Munakata
        Shrine is the same as that from 坊津 Bōnotsu in former Satsuma province (today Kagoshima). The
        body of the stele carries a colophon reading 大宋囗囗囗年 , probably 承久二年 (1220). The stone is
        therefore from China, Ningbo 寧波. </abstract>
